name: 02-Data Description and Preparation
content:
Data Description and Preparation

Data Source:

  • Derived from network monitoring systems and fault logging databases maintained by telecom operators.

Data Format:

  • Tabular format (CSV or database tables).
  • Each row represents a unique fault or event.

Data Dictionaries:

  • id – Unique identifier for each record.
  • location – Location of the fault/event.
  • severity_type – Category of severity type associated with the fault.
  • resource_type – Type of equipment or resource affected.
  • log_feature – Log attribute related to the event.
  • volume – Count of log occurrences for the feature.
  • event_type – Event classification (e.g., outage, error).
  • fault_severity – Target variable (0 = low, 1 = critical).

Data Preparation Steps:

  1. Data Cleaning:
  • Address missing values and remove inconsistencies.
  • Normalize categorical fields (severity_type, resource_type, event_type).
  1. Feature Engineering:
  • Aggregate event volumes per resource/location.
  • Encode categorical variables using one-hot encoding.
  • Generate derived metrics such as event density by location.
  1. Transformation:
  • Standardize numerical features (volume).
  • Split into training and testing datasets for supervised learning.

﻿
